Are you washing your hands?
Scientists have discovered that washing your hands will change your mood.
The experiment was attended by 98 people, divided into three groups.
The first two were tasked with solving an insoluble task.
Of course, they both failed.
But the group that washed their hands after the setback seemed much more optimistic than the one where its participants did not wash their hands.
The "washed hands" group also performed better than the other in the next test.
Still, those who washed their hands achieved worse results in other tests than those who didn't.
The results of the "washed" were at the level of the third group, whose participants had not seen any previous failure.
According to psychologists, the results of the test indicate that body purity removes really negative feelings after failure.
At the same time, however, motivation decreases, the testers need to concentrate much more in the next exams.
If we transferred the results of the research to the Czechs, we would probably be the most optimistic after returning from the toilet.
After using the toilet, not only one percent of Czechs and Czechs wash their hands, but it is already a fifth on the way by public transport.
