Even any pay freeze in the world would not avert a smourding of Europe's petrochemical industry with cheap US shale oil.
The result is a simmering rebellion, especially in France, once an enthusiastic supporter of the EU.
After the war, the political elite in France saw the EU as a tool to keep Germany in check and allow Paris to stand on Washington's level in the world.
