Before the elections, a long-simmering dispute between two wings fighting for influence within the Ostrava ČSSD was fully in flames.
It all culminated when the Mayor of Ostrava, Petr Kajnar, appealed to the court for undemocratic listing of candidates.
Still, the actors in the case did not want to comment too much so as not to damage the party even more before the elections.
But now the voters' votes are counted.
The leadership of the Ostrava ČSSD called on the Mayor of Ostrava to step down from the party on Monday evening and will probably also push for him to lose his post.
